Usage: set_max_capacitance [-help] <capacitance_limit> <object_list>
                           [-clock_path] [-data_path] [-fall] [-override]
                           [-rise]

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
<capacitance_limit>       # Value for the maximum capacitance limit
                          # (float, required)
<object_list>             # List of objects: ports, instance pins, library cell
                          # pins, clocks or current_design (string, required)
-clock_path               # Apply the capacitance limit constraint to pins in
                          # the clock network of the clocks defined in
                          # object_list (bool, optional)
-data_path                # Apply the capacitance limit constraint to data path
                          # pins, where the path is launched by the clocks
                          # defined in object_list (bool, optional)
-fall                     # Apply the capacitance limit constraint to falling
                          # capacitances (bool, optional)
-override                 # Overrides capacitance limit from other sources
                          # namely library/constraints (bool, optional)
-rise                     # Apply the capacitance limit constraint to rising
                          # capacitances (bool, optional)